The White House has released a report on the economic benefits of investing in transportation infrastructure. The report highlights the potential for innovation in the infrastructure sector, with new technologies and approaches promising gains in productivity, efficiency, and resilience. The President is urging Congress to take action to avoid a lapse in funding for the Highway Trust Fund, which could lead to the insolvency of numerous projects. The White House has also released an interactive transportation map that shows the condition of roads and bridges in each state and the potential consequences if Congress fails to act.